<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 5000 9100 9200 9400 9900 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 5000, 5000i, 9000, 9000i - TROUBLESHOOTING - TACHOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TACHOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08207x_11.xml" xrefid="x082076a">TACHOMETER</hotlnk>
                for operation description of tachometer circuits.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x082077a">
            <title>Inspecting And Adjusting the Engine Speed Sensor (Mech. Engines Only)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect engine harness connector (111) from the sensor. Loosen the locknut and remove
                    the sensor. The harness connector and sensor should be free of damage or corrosion. Remove any metal
                    shavings or debris from the sensor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the sensor, turn in until the sensor contacts the flywheel gear, then back
                    out
                    <emph type="bold">one full turn.</emph>
                    Tighten lock nut to 15 ft-lbs. (20.3 N&#183; m). This assures that the sensor is adjusted properly
                    for the next test.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>To perform this test, construct two test leads using terminals (P/N 1680205C1) and suitable length of
                16GA wire. Install terminals on one end and alligator clips on the other.
            </para>
            <table id="t0820712" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Inspecting And Adjusting the Engine Speed Sensor (Mech. Engines Only)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.52in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.61in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With sensor (111) disconnected, use test lead to measure resistance to ground at
                                    both
                                    <emph type="bold">sensor</emph>
                                    terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Sensor terminals to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the engine speed sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Use test leads and measure resistance between engine speed sensor terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Between sensor terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>600 to 900 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the engine speed sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Perform sensor output test below.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>> or = 2.0 AC volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Engine speed sensor checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the engine speed sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Engine Speed Sensor Output Test</title>
            </para>
            <para>This test checks for proper AC voltage output from the engine speed sensor. Improper adjustment will
                cause LOW, ERRATIC, or NO sensor output.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>EXTREME CAUTION should be used to prevent personal injury resulting from contact with engine
                        rotating parts when connecting test leads.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Use AC voltmeter. Connect meter leads to sensor test leads.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Run engine at idle speed, with transmission in neutral. Measure voltage across the two sensor
                        terminals.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sensor output should be 2.0 AC volts or more.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Engine Speed Signal To Speedometer/Tachometer Module (Mechanical Engine Only)</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To test data link circuits between the Speedometer/Tachometer module and ECM with electronic
                        engines, refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Group 08 - ELECTRICAL, Electronic Engine Controls</emph>
                        in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Perform
                <hotlnk xrefid="x082077a">Inspecting and Adjusting the Engine Speed Sensor</hotlnk>
                before performing this test!
            </para>
            <table id="t0820713" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Engine Speed Signal To Speedometer/Tachometer Module (Mechanical Engine Only)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.47in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove connector (421) from Speedometer/ Tachometer module and disconnect engine
                                    harness conn. (111) from engine speed sensor. At connector (421) measure resistance
                                    to ground at circuits 48A and 48B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 48A and 48B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with less than 100K resistance, between
                                    connectors (421) and (111), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (421) measure resistance between circuits 48A and 48B and between all
                                    other circuits in the connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 48A and 48B and all other circuits.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short between any circuits with less than 100K resistance between
                                    terminals, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (111) use test lead to jumper circuit 48A to ground. At connector
                                    (421) measure resistance to ground at circuit 48A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 48A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60;or = 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 48A between connectors (421) to (111), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (111) use test lead to jumper circuit 48B to ground. At connector
                                    (421) measure resistance to ground at circuit 48B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 48B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60;or = 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 48B between connectors (111) and (421), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>The engine speed sensor and connecting circuits check good. If speedometer and
                                    tachometer gauges were switched (see
                                    <hotlnk document="s08207x_40.xml" xrefid="x0820708">GAUGE CIRCUIT
                                        TROUBLESHOOTING</hotlnk>) then replace the Speedometer/Tachometer module.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
